<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1079] DocValues cleanup: constructor &amp; getInnerArray()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1079</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;DocValues constructor taking a numDocs parameter is not very clean.&lt;br/&gt;
Get rid of this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, it&apos;s optional getInnerArray() method is not very clean.&lt;br/&gt;
This is necessary for better testing, but currently tests will fail if it is not implemented.&lt;br/&gt;
Modify it to throw UnSupportedOp exception (rather than returning an empty array).&lt;br/&gt;
Modify tests to not fail but just warn if the tested iml does not override it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These changes should make it easier to implement DocValues for other ValueSource&apos;s, e.g. above payloads, with or without caching.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
